Presbyterians approve National Council of Churches bailout
</P>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- After the new chief executive of the
National Council of Churches said he had installed financial
controls and ''stopped the hemorrhaging,'' Presbyterian Church
leaders approved a $500,000 gift to help the council meet a $2
million deficit for 1999.
</P>
<P>
   But Presbyterian executives said the gift is contingent on other
denominations in the council meeting the rest of the deficit, and a
balanced council budget for 2000.
</P>
