   The Presbyterians also ordered a comprehensive review of the
church council and other ecumenical agencies every three years.
Presbyterian News Service said more than 1,000 communications to
headquarters ran 9-to-1 against the bailout for the church council.
</P>
<P>
   Presbyterian executives planned to send church members a
''pastoral letter'' explaining the decision, as well as the
financial loss the Presbyterians themselves suffered at a New
Year's youth rally.
</P>
