<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-02 22:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Abduction ends in suspect's surrender  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP)-- The alleged armed abduction of two women
ended peacefully early Thursday evening after the suspect turned
himself in to state police.
</P>
<P>
   Adam Bennefield, 22, of Buffalo faces charges including two
counts of kidnapping, one count of unauthorized use of a motor
vehicle and criminal possession of a weapon.
</P>
<P>
   Bennefield allegedly used a shotgun to force two women from
their car into a stolen car about 9 a.m. He then drove on
Interstate 190 from Buffalo to Grand Island, where one of the women
jumped out, state police said. She was not seriously hurt.
</P>
<P>
   State police said the second woman was also not harmed.
</P>
<P>
   Police described Bennefield as an acquaintance of one of the
women, whose identities were not released.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators were able to establish contact with Bennefield and
arrange for him to turn himself in with the help of his family and
his attorney.
</P>
<P>
   Bennefield will be arraigned in Buffalo City Court Friday
morning.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
